1.title: Help a Spider
1.plot: Gasp tries to help a meek spider gain some self-esteem, all the while fighting his own phobic reactions.

2.title: Frankenkitty
2.plot: Gasp experiments with Ginger's school science project to make Dogbox smarter and, in the process, turns Catflap into a mindless monster.

3.title: Fish Stick
3.plot: Gasp, experimenting with mind-control techniques while babysitting, panics when he thinks he's accidentally turned Winston into a fish stick.

4.title: Home and Host
4.plot: Gasp has a dilemma on his fins when getting rid of Dogbox's fleas means finding the cheerful little flea family a new home.

6.title: My Pet Rocks
6.plot: To make Ginger proud, Gasp enlists the pets to help him make a video of himself to enter in the 'My Pet Totally Rocks' TV show contest.

13.title: Pets for Pets
13.plot: The pets become jealous of Fred and Ginger's new electronic virtual pets, only to become addicted themselves when they try to hide them.

26.title: Thermostat Wars
26.plot: The cold-blooded pets compete with the warm-blooded pets over control of Dad's new heating and cooling unit.

32.title: For the Love of Dog
32.plot: The pets are in a frenzy trying to do Fred's chores for him when they overhear Mum threatening to send Dogbox away if he doesn't shape up.

48.title: Hooray for Hamsterwood
48.plot: The pets are so in awe of Horatio, the charismatic class guinea pig Ginger's brought home for the weekend, that they let him out of his cage.

imdb.plot outline: Laughs, Lunacy and Logic - wait, scratch that last part - conspire in this situation comedy series about a larger-than-life little goldfish named Gasp, whose imagination is as big as his heart. Based on the successful GASP!, ZAPT!, SPLAT!, SQUISH!, CRASH. CHOMP. series of comic books by Australian author/illustrator/genius Terry Denton, this fin-twitchingly funny series follows the zany antics of a goldfish and his family-pet 'cousins' left home alone when Mum, Dad and their two kids, Ginger and Fred, have gone off to work, school or play. Ever wondered what pets get up to when there are no humans around to spoil the fun? This is the place to find out. From all-pet singing/dancing revues to Arctic expeditions through the freezer, anything can happen in this house -- and usually does.
